                              <img src="assets/img/iconh/20.png" alt="Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)" width="35px" loading="lazy">&nbsp;&nbsp;
                              <div class="question-text-wrapper">
                                 <span class="question-text">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) Chopta Chandrashila Trek </span>
                                 <span class="question-subheading">Your Curiosity, Our Commitment</span>
                              </div>
                              <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                           </button>
  
                           
                           <div class="detaildropdown-content">
                                                                                          <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>1. What is the Chopta – Chandrashila – Tungnath Trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    The Chopta – Chandrashila – Tungnath Trek is a scenic Himalayan trek in Uttarakhand, India. It combines lush green meadows, dense forests, and snow-covered peaks with spiritual experiences at the Tungnath Temple, the highest Shiva temple in the world, and a panoramic view from Chandrashila Peak.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>2. Where is Chopta located?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Chopta is located in the Rudraprayag district of Uttarakhand, at an altitude of around 2,680 meters. It is often called the “Mini Switzerland of India” due to its breathtaking landscapes.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>3. How do I reach Chopta?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    • By Road: The nearest major town is Rishikesh or Dehradun. From there, taxis or buses are available.
• By Rail: The nearest railway station is Rishikesh.
• By Air: The nearest airport is Jolly Grant Airport, Dehradun.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>4. What is the best time for the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    • Summer (April – June): Pleasant weather, clear skies, and wildflowers in full bloom.
• Monsoon (July – September): Not recommended due to landslides and slippery trails.
• Autumn (October – November): Crisp air, ideal trekking conditions, and fewer crowds.
• Winter (December – March): Snow-covered trails, ideal for snow treks and stunning Himalayan views.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>5. What is the duration of the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Typically, the trek takes 3–4 days depending on your starting point and pace.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>6. What is the difficulty level of the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    This is a moderate trek suitable for beginners with basic fitness. The trails are well-marked, but steep climbs to Tungnath and Chandrashila require stamina and proper trekking gear.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>9. Do I need any permits for the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    No special permits are required for Indian citizens. Foreign tourists may need to register at local authorities, but generally, Chopta – Chandrashila – Tungnath is an open trekking area.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>10. Is there accommodation available on the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Yes, options include:
• Campsites in Chopta
• Guesthouses and lodges in Chopta and nearby villages
• Homestays along the trail for an authentic local experience                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>11. Are guides necessary?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Hiring a local trekking guide is optional but recommended for first-time trekkers. They ensure safety, help with navigation, and provide insights about flora, fauna, and local culture.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>12. How fit do I need to be?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Moderate fitness is sufficient. Regular walking, light jogging, or stair climbing before the trek will help. Steep sections and high altitudes require endurance and proper pacing.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>13. What wildlife can I see on the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    The area is home to:
• Himalayan Monal (state bird of Uttarakhand)
• Musk deer
• Various species of pheasants, butterflies, and wildflowers                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>14. Can the trek be done in winter?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Yes, winter treks are popular for snow-covered landscapes and Chandrashila snow views. Proper winter trekking gear is essential, including insulated jackets, gloves, and trekking poles with snow grips.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>15. Is the trek suitable for children?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Children above 10–12 years with decent fitness can attempt the trek. Shorter distances and moderate climbs make it family-friendly, but supervision is necessary on steep or snowy sections.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                                                       </div>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="col-12 col-md-4 col-lg-4 col-xxl-4">
